  "prompt": "What does \u201csocially inept\u201d mean?",
  "response": "The term \u201csocially inept\u201d refers to a person who lacks the skills or awareness to interact effectively with others in social situations. This can manifest in various ways, such as difficulty understanding social cues, inappropriate behavior, awkwardness, or an inability to engage in normal conversation. Socially inept individuals may struggle to build or maintain relationships, often unintentionally offending or alienating others due to their lack of social finesse. \n\nIt\u2019s important to note that social ineptitude can stem from various factors, including anxiety, lack of experience, neurological differences (e.g., autism spectrum disorder), or simply a lack of confidence in social settings. It\u2019s not necessarily a permanent trait, and social skills can often be improved with practice, guidance, or support.",
